solution:
Since the sum of the angles at any point on a line is $180^\circ,$ then we find that \begin{align*}
\angle GAE &= 180^\circ - 120^\circ = 60^\circ, \\
\angle GEA &= 180^\circ - 80^\circ = 100^\circ.
\end{align*}

